
	tiny-pf: implementation of `fprintf` function from libc for x86_64

DEPENDENCIES
	This library depends on `xvargs` (github.com/h0p3so/xvargs/) to parse variadic
	arguments

API
	* TINY_PF_LONG_BOOL_FMT: if defined, %b will be parsed into 'true' or 'false', 'T' or 'F'
	will be used otherwise (by default is not defined)

	* tiny_pf(fd, format, ...) -> usize (number of bytes written)
	          |    `      ~~~ pushed into stack (xvargs)
            rdi     `- rsi

	- fd: unsigned 32 bit which represents the file descriptor. tiny_pf will output to such fd.
	- format: string literal which specifies the content to be printed and the formatting
		%%		prints '%' literal
		%c		format for a character
		%s		format for a string
		%d		format for a signed integer
		%u		format for a unsigned integer
		%x		hexadecimal integer formatting
		%o		octal integer formatting
		%#*		right aligment
			#: unsigned int representing width
			*: integer formatting (d, u, x o)
		%0*		zero padding
			0: literal '0' is mandatory
			*: integer formatting (d, u, x o)
		%-#*	left aligment
			-: literal '-' is mandatory
			#: unsigned int representing width
			*: integer formatting (d, u, x o)
		%b		format for boolean (prints TINY_PF_LONG_BOOL_FMT)
	- extra arguments: values to which formats specified in `format` string will be
	mapped to. Remember this library heavily depends on xvargs, therefore all these
	arguments needs to be pushed into the stack in the reverse order they need to be
	used

